Executive Profile
James H. Amos Jr.Operating Partner, Snow Phipps Group, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. James H. Amos, also Known as Jim. Jr., serves as a Managing Partner at Eagle Alliance Partners. Mr. Amos served as the Chief Executive Officer of Planet Smoothie, LLC until December 31, 2012. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Tasti D-Lite, LLC from 2007 to December 31, 2012. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Sona MedSpa International, Inc. since May 2004. He served as President and the Chief Executive Officer at Mail Boxes Etc. (MBE) since October ... 1996 until September 30, 2002. He served as the Chief Operating Officer of Mail Boxes Etc. since October 1996. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of the Brice Group in Dallas for eight years. He served as an Operating Partner at Snow Phipps Group, LLC. Mr. Amos was responsible for specialty franchising at Snow Phipps. Mr. Amos is a renowned franchise executive. He serves as Chairman of The Board of APFI. He served as the Executive Chairman of Sona MedSpa International, Inc. since May 2004. He served as the Chairman Emeritus at Mail Boxes Etc. (MBE). In 2001, Mr. Amos was instrumental in orchestrating the sale of MBE to United Parcel Services who subsequently renamed the system, The UPS Store. Throughout his career, he has been a leader in the franchising industry. A former Marine Corps captain and veteran of two combat tours in Vietnam, he received 12 decorations, including the Purple Heart and Vietnamese Cross of Gallantry. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Sona MedSpa; and the International Franchise Association (IFA). He has more than 30 years of experience He serves as Chairman of The Franchise Advisory Board at Agile Pursuits Franchising Inc. He serves as Chairman of the Board of Tasti D-Lite, LLC. He has been an Independent Director of The Joint Corp. since September 17, 2015. Mr. Amos serves as Member of the Advisory Board at Left Behind Games Inc. and Research and Management Corporation. He serves as a Director of NuMarkets, LLC. He serves as a Member of executive council at American Securities. He served as a Director of Sona MedSpa International, Inc. Mr. Amos is the author of two books, Focus or Failure: American at the Crossroads and The Memorial. The latter, chosen by the American Library Association as “One of the Best Books of the Year in 1990, has been re-printed in 2001. He has also contributed to The Entrepreneur's Creed-The Principles & Passions of 20 Successful Entrepreneurs and The Transparent Leader. His third book, The Complete Idiot's Guide to Franchising released by Penguin Press in August 2005. He also received the 2012 Nashville Business Leader Legend Award. Mr. Amos has been recognized in “Marquis Who's Who in America“, “Who's Who in American Executives“, “Who's Who in Finance and Industry“, “Who's Who in American Authors“ and “The International Authors and Writers Who's Who“. Additionally, he serves on the Boards of The National Veteran's Administration, The Marine Military Academy, The Marine Corps Heritage Foundation, Meineke Mufflers, Franchise Alliance Finance, The University of Missouri, The International Franchise Association and Ken Blanchard's Faith Walk Leadership Board. Mr. Amos has served on or is serving on the board of directors of Meineke Car Care Centers, Oreck Corporation, Zig Ziglar Corporation, WSI of Canada, SkinPhd, The HealthStore Foundation and Ken Blanchard’s Faith Walk Leadership Foundation. He was a guest speak at Yale and Harvard in 2013 and also for the National Restaurant Association, the National Association of Development Companies, The International Franchise Association convention and Prayer Breakfasts, the “New Normal Entrepreneurs” conference for Crown Financial Ministries, Secret Knock. Most recently, he was nominated for the International Franchise Association’s Hall of Fame award. He was honored as the 1998 Scholar-in-Residence and in 2000 and 2003 with the Distinguished Alumni Award. Mr. Amos received his Degree in Political Science from the University of Missouri at Columbia.Read Full Background




